#, no-wrap
msgid "Controlling the Management Interface of Your Beans"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:11
msgid ""
"In the example in the "
"xref:integration/jmx/exporting.adoc#jmx-exporting-registration-behavior[preceding "
"section], you had little control over the management interface of your "
"bean. All of the `public` properties and methods of each exported bean were "
"exposed as JMX attributes and operations, respectively. To exercise "
"finer-grained control over exactly which properties and methods of your "
"exported beans are actually exposed as JMX attributes and operations, Spring "
"JMX provides a comprehensive and extensible mechanism for controlling the "
"management interfaces of your beans."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the `MBeanInfoAssembler` API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Behind the scenes, the `MBeanExporter` delegates to an implementation of the "
"`org.springframework.jmx.export.assembler.MBeanInfoAssembler` API, which is "
"responsible for defining the management interface of each bean that is "
"exposed.  The default implementation, "
"`org.springframework.jmx.export.assembler.SimpleReflectiveMBeanInfoAssembler`, "
"defines a management interface that exposes all public properties and "
"methods (as you saw in the examples in the preceding sections). Spring "
"provides two additional implementations of the `MBeanInfoAssembler` "
"interface that let you control the generated management interface by using "
"either source-level metadata or any arbitrary interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using Source-level Metadata: Java Annotations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:38
msgid ""
"By using the `MetadataMBeanInfoAssembler`, you can define the management "
"interfaces for your beans by using source-level metadata. The reading of "
"metadata is encapsulated by the "
"`org.springframework.jmx.export.metadata.JmxAttributeSource` "
"interface. Spring JMX provides a default implementation that uses Java "
"annotations, namely "
"`org.springframework.jmx.export.annotation.AnnotationJmxAttributeSource`. "
"You must configure the `MetadataMBeanInfoAssembler` with an implementation "
"instance of the `JmxAttributeSource` interface for it to function correctly, "
"since there is no default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:45
msgid ""
"To mark a bean for export to JMX, you should annotate the bean class with "
"the `@ManagedResource` annotation. You must annotate each method you wish to "
"expose as an operation with the `@ManagedOperation` annotation and annotate "
"each property you wish to expose with the `@ManagedAttribute` "
"annotation. When annotating properties, you can omit either the annotation "
"of the getter or the setter to create a write-only or read-only attribute, "
"respectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/integration/jmx/interface.adoc:48
msgid ""
"A `@ManagedResource`-annotated bean must be public, as must the methods "
"exposing operations or attributes."
msgstr ""

